			<p>If the e4 gene is present, a person&rsquo;s risk goes up - but never to 100%.</p>
			<P>It&rsquo;s important to keep in mind that:</P>
			<ul>
				<li>some people who have the e4 gene will not develop Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease.</li>
				<li>some people who do not have the e4 gene will develop Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease.</li>
				<li>Researchers believe there are additional genes associated with Alzheimer&rsquo;s that we have not yet identified.</li>
